I can not tell you how many times I was awoken at 3am by the heavy bass (which usually shook my sixth floor windows) from a car owned by a student athlete or the number of times myself and others were forced to call the RA's to break up fights or drunken parties that were being held in the elevator lobbies by the same. Not only that, often times these disturbances occurred either late at night or during finals week, if not both. 

Now I know that this isn't necessarily the case for every student athlete, and I'm sure that those who perpetrate these offenses are more of a vocal minority, however the main issue I have here is that the repeated use of the term "division I athlete" implies a certain level of superiority over the rest of us. Perhaps you don't feel this way, which I hope is the case, but We ALL deserve the same common courtesy and respect, not just those who blessed with the ability to play a sport at a high level. There should not be a double standard, and that was and is the point I was trying to make. Just please don't pretend like there is a lack of conscientiousness in only one direction, because I can assure you I am not the only person who feels that it goes both ways.
